(66, 12, 1, 42, 21, 11, 11, NULL, 'Signs and Wonders in Heaven', 'This connection highlights the theme of great signs from heaven. Both passages emphasize celestial imagery, with Revelation mentioning a woman ''clothed with the sun'' and Luke referencing ''great signs shall there be from heaven.''', 'theme', 0.363, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(66, 12, 1, 19, 84, 11, 11, 'clothed with the sun', 'Connection of Light and Protection', 'This connection highlights the imagery of the sun in both passages. In Revelation, the woman is ''clothed with the sun,'' while in Psalms, the Lord is described as ''a sun and shield,'' emphasizing divine light and protection.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(66, 12, 1, 22, 6, 10, 10, NULL, 'Connection of Celestial Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize celestial imagery, with the woman in Revelation described as ''clothed with the sun'' and the one in Song of Solomon compared to ''the sun'' and ''the moon.'' This connection highlights the use of heavenly symbols to convey beauty and significance.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(66, 12, 1, 23, 60, 19, 20, 'clothed with the sun', 'Light and Glory Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of light, where Revelation describes a woman clothed with the sun, symbolizing divine glory, while Isaiah speaks of the Lord as an everlasting light, replacing the sun and moon. Both passages emphasize the transformative power of God''s presence as a source of illumination and glory.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
