(66, 12, 3, 23, 27, 1, 1, 'dragon', 'Connection Between Dragons', 'Both passages emphasize the imagery of a dragon, representing chaos and evil. Revelation''s ''great red dragon'' and Isaiah''s ''dragon that is in the sea'' highlight a thematic link in their portrayal of malevolent forces.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(66, 12, 3, 23, 51, 9, 9, NULL, 'Connection of the Dragon Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the imagery of a dragon, with Revelation depicting a great red dragon and Isaiah referencing a dragon in the context of God''s power. This connection highlights the theme of divine confrontation against chaotic forces.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(66, 12, 4, 27, 8, 9, 12, NULL, 'Connection of Host and Stars', 'Both passages emphasize the casting down of stars and the host of heaven, indicating a common theme of celestial conflict and opposition. The imagery of the dragon and the little horn suggests a shared motif of malevolent forces acting against divine order.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(66, 12, 4, 66, 12, 9, 9, 'the dragon', 'Connection of the Dragon''s Role', 'Both passages emphasize the dragon''s identity and actions. In Revelation 12:4, the dragon''s tail casts down stars, while Revelation 12:9 identifies him as the Devil who deceives the world and is cast out.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(66, 12, 4, 43, 8, 44, 44, 'the dragon stood before the woman', 'Connection of the Devil''s Nature', 'This connection highlights the dragon''s role as a deceiver and adversary in Revelation, paralleling the description of the devil as a liar and murderer in John. Both passages emphasize the destructive and malevolent nature of the devil.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
