(66, 12, 5, 66, 19, 15, 15, 'rule all nations with a rod of iron', 'Connection of Ruling with Iron', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of ruling nations with a rod of iron. The first passage introduces the child destined to rule, while the second passage describes the figure who will execute this rule. This connection highlights a continuity in the depiction of authority and judgment.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(66, 12, 5, 66, 2, 26, 27, 'with a rod of iron', 'Connection of Ruling with Iron', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of ruling nations with a rod of iron. The SOURCE verse describes the child destined to rule, while the TARGET passage promises power to the overcomer to rule similarly. This connection highlights a shared motif of authority and dominion.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(66, 12, 5, 19, 2, 9, 10, 'rod of iron', 'Connection of Iron Rule', 'This connection highlights the theme of ruling with a rod of iron found in both passages. Revelation 12:5 speaks of a child destined to rule all nations with a rod of iron, while Psalms 2:9 emphasizes breaking nations with a rod of iron.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(66, 12, 5, 23, 7, 14, 14, 'a man child, who was to rule', 'Connection of Prophetic Births', 'Both passages emphasize the birth of a significant child. Revelation speaks of a child destined to rule, while Isaiah foretells a virgin conceiving a son, highlighting the importance of these births in biblical prophecy.', 'prophecy', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(66, 12, 5, 33, 5, 3, 3, 'who was to rule all nations', 'Connection of Birth and Rule', 'This connection highlights the theme of a significant birth leading to rulership. Both passages emphasize the idea of a child being born who will have authority, with Micah referencing the time of travail and Revelation mentioning the child who will rule all nations.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(66, 12, 5, 40, 1, 25, 25, 'who was to rule all nations', 'Connection of Jesus'' Birth and Rule', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of the child born to rule. Revelation speaks of a child destined to ''rule all nations,'' while Matthew identifies this child as Jesus, affirming his royal role.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(66, 12, 5, 24, 31, 22, 22, NULL, 'Connection of Woman and Child', 'This connection highlights the theme of a woman giving birth to a significant child. Both passages emphasize the role of a woman in relation to a man who has a divine purpose.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
