(66, 13, 2, 9, 17, 34, 37, NULL, 'Beasts and Deliverance Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the imagery of a lion and a bear, representing danger and opposition. David''s victory over these beasts parallels the beast in Revelation, which symbolizes a powerful adversary. This connection highlights the theme of divine deliverance from formidable foes.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
