(66, 13, 14, 66, 19, 20, 20, NULL, 'Connection of Deception and Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the role of deception through miracles associated with the beast and the false prophet. The first passage introduces the act of deceiving those who worship the image of the beast, while the second describes the judgment of the deceivers.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(66, 13, 14, 27, 11, 36, 36, 'deceiveth them that dwell on the earth', 'Connection of Deception and Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of a powerful figure deceiving others and exalting himself. Both passages depict a leader who performs miraculous acts and speaks against God, emphasizing their authority and influence over the people.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(66, 13, 14, 53, 2, 4, 4, 'deceiveth them that dwell on the earth', 'Connection of Deception and Worship', 'Both passages emphasize the act of deception and the elevation of a figure claiming divinity. Revelation 13:14 speaks of an image made to the beast, while 2 Thessalonians 2:4 describes one who sits in the temple of God, showing himself as God.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(66, 13, 14, 12, 20, 7, 7, NULL, 'Healing and Deception Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of miraculous acts leading to significant outcomes. In Revelation, miracles deceive people into creating an image, while in 2 Kings, a simple act of applying figs leads to healing.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
